---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../site.config';
---

<Base title="About" description="What this library is, how curation works, and who is behind it.">
  <p class="font-mono text-[11px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-accent">The mission</p>
  <h1 class="mt-2 font-display text-4xl font-medium tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink-900 sm:text-5xl">About {SITE.name}</h1>

  <div class="workflow-body mt-5 max-w-xl">
    <p>
      <strong>{SITE.name} is a workflow library, not a tool directory.</strong> Tool lists tell you
      what exists; they don't tell you how real people get real work done. Every entry here is a
      reproducible recipe: a job to be done, the exact steps, the exact prompts, the tools used, and a link to the original human source as proof.
    </p>

    <h2>How curation works</h2>
    <p>
      A daily automated pipeline scans Reddit, Hacker News, Dev.to, YouTube, GitHub and selected
      newsletters for workflows people actually used. Each candidate is scored against a strict
      quality rubric, vague hype and tool announcements are discarded; only clear, reproducible
      workflows are published. Every workflow links back to its original source and credits the
      author.
    </p>

    <h2>What the badges mean</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Sourced</strong>, found in the wild; the original post is embedded as proof.</li>
      <li><strong>Tested</strong>, personally reproduced by us, step by step.</li>
      <li><strong>Community-verified</strong>, confirmed by readers (coming later).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Built for Nigeria first</h2>
    <p>
      This library is built mobile-first and data-light, with a "free tools only" filter and
      Nigeria-specific notes on workflows (free-tier viability, data usage, local payment
      compatibility). Global users are welcome, useful is useful everywhere.
    </p>

    <h2>Who's behind it</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} is built and run by Opq. Found a workflow that should be here?
      <a href="/submit/">Submit it</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
